    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but the math doesnt add up like that. if the end state for everyone is the same, the net value is zero. if i'm just adding more struggle to an already empty equation, isn't it more \"rational\" to just exit? it feels like people just use \"meaning\" as a way to ignore the logic of the void.",
